main event: A witness observed one light, then one white light and a reddish-white light which appeared to be connected, over Miamisburg, Ohio on March 19, 1968.
interesting points: The witness said the objects appeared to be circling the golf course and felt they were low in the sky.
The Air Force contacted local helicopter services, but none had any aircraft in the air at the time of the sighting.
The Monsanto plant guards did not report seeing anything unusual during their shift.
The Air Force concluded there was insufficient data to evaluate the sighting.
The Air Force requested the witness complete an additional form (AF Form 117) to provide more information.
